{"id":53525,"title":"Gestational diabetes: real risks beyond the controversy.","abstract":"Gestational diabetes has been a controversial subject in the midwifery community for many years. While the diagnosis and disease can be debated, one statistic remains without controversy: women who meet the diagnostic criteria for gestational diabetes are at risk for developing type 2 diabetes after delivery. This article discusses the importance of postpartum follow-up, whether gestational diabetes screening was completed in pregnancy or not, and what a midwife can do to lower her clients' risk of developing type 2 diabetes.","date":"2014-02-11","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24511847","annotations":[{"name":"Gestational diabetes","weight":0.906012,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gestational_diabetes"},{"name":"Pregnancy","weight":0.816331,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pregnancy"},{"name":"Diabetes mellitus","weight":0.814954,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.768313,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.725218,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Diabetes mellitus type 2","weight":0.523718,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus_type_2"},{"name":"Midwifery","weight":0.424595,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midwifery"},{"name":"Woman","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Woman"},{"name":"Screening (medicine)","weight":0.132876,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screening_(medicine)"},{"name":"Postnatal","weight":0.129429,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Postnatal"},{"name":"Gestational age","weight":0.0561009,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gestational_age"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0339217,"wik